env PAGER=cat man timing_report_check_timing_unconstrained_endpoin ts_due_to_constants
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_report...e_to_constants(25.10)    timing_report...e_to_constants(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_check_timing_unconstrained_endpoints_due_to_constants

Syntax
       timing_report_check_timing_unconstrained_endpoints_due_to_constants
       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Enables  the software to flag unconstrained signals arriving at the end
       points due to case analysis.

       When set to false, the check_timing command output will  show  warnings
       for the unconstrained endpoints.

       When set to true, the command output will also show warnings for uncon-
       strained  endpoints  due  to  case  analysis  under the subcategory un-
       cons_endpoints_due_to_case_analysis. For more details,  see  check_tim-
       ing.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

